	   <tr><td colspan=2>My response was tongue-in-cheek in that prior to L30 the amount of damage being dished out pales in comparison to what will occur once that magic level is made.<br>Is there an actual "Touch of Death"?&nbsp;&nbsp;No. Anyone who plays this game for any period of time will find that quite apparent. But it will seem like there is a ToD when the 10 point offensive skill increase takes place.  And this is the moment we impatiently wait for when we choose to make a monk, isn't it? <br><br>For those of you who read these posts of mine, please bear in mind that more frequently than not I editorialize rather than pass out specific information on questions being asked.  After all, I guarantee that for any question posed there are at least five answers to the VERY same question asked in the previous three pages.<br><br>Pilapeu, I recognize my humor isn't what everybody's tastes run to, but personally I would gladly read a post by Chimi, Gorthin, Tymothy, or someone who displays a creative approach to answering a question which has been asked twenty times previously in other posts as opposed to a flat response that shows no flicker of funniness.  In turn, I hope in some fashion my warped sense of humor will make others laugh as those who I mentioned above have elicited everything from a smile to side-splitting laughter from me as I identified with the predicaments in which they found themselves.<br><br>I hope you don't take this as an attack on yourself, but as an explanation for why I write in the manner I choose.  For that, I offer my apologies up front for things I say that are offensive.  Indeed, I frequently have to pull my punches in these articles since my natural sense of humor is acerbic or venomous to the point of nastiness. While that may be funny, it is funny at someone elses' expense.  And to me, that makes it not funny at all.<br>Thanks for this opportunity to get this off my chest.<br>:D<br><br>--Pusbag Infection, who carries a box of Arm & Hammer around with him to neutralize all that acidicy pouring out in his posts.<br><br>/em Pusbag starts fizzing as he pours the baking soda on top of himself.<br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
